data.text:
I own Shadey Acres, a five star vacation home rental in Jupiter Farms. I have lived in Jupiter Farms for 34 years and have been going to Annie’s with my husband, kids and grandkids for the 22 years it’s been open. I recommend Annie’s to my guests.

It’s a small Italian Ice parlor where you can go to the outside window or inside where there are a couple of tables.  The venue is old and not fancy but the frozen yogurt (made on site) is the creamiest and freshest that I have ever eaten, and has been consistently so over all these years.  Their Gelatos, (Italian ice and frozen yogurt layered confection) are my favorites.  There is wide choice of flavored Ices. They also serve hot dogs and pretzels.

For a real treat go to Annie’s, you won’t regret it!

data.title: Homemade Ices
data.text: The best homehade ices in Florida.   Always fresh and delicious.  Any flavor you can think of they have. And great custard too..

data.title: Cool refreshing Italian Ice
data.text: Annie's Italian Ice is our go to place after a hot afternoon in the sun on the beach.  The kids look forward to their icy treat and look forward to the different flavor options each day.

data.title: Keep it Cool
data.text: This place has the best Italian ice and has great service. Have been going there for many years.Great place to take the kids.

data.title: real Italian ices
data.text: reminded me of home (NYC) It was so good that was worth the traffic to get there .. plan on spending a lot of time there this summer :-)

data.title: Best lil place in Jupiter for Italian Ices
data.text: This is one of the smallest but best lil places for that cold treat... I suggest it.. its a must try... parking is in the back and if u don't look for it you will pass it... its a good place for Italian Ices and Ice Cream

data.title: Great find for water ice
data.text: Bought water ice and a quart to take home. Easy,great ice and many flavors.We enjoyed the mango and  will return. They know what they are doing.

data.title: Great italian ices!
data.text: We went here for a sweet treat after dinner.  The italian ice was delicious.  Kind of soft, fluffy style rather than hard.  Lots of flavors to choose from.  They also have ice cream and some fast food (hot dogs, nachos, pretzels, etc.) although all we tried were the ices.  I would go back again for sure!
